    "client_msg_id": "ba23e4b8-f7c6-4ca7-878b-1ad11872a3dd",
    "text": "meta note — this discussion has had a _lot_ of links pasted without any explanation or context. this has two issues:\n\n1. i don't know what many of those links are about (eg: the HN and YT links). it'd be nicer for my experience reading your post if you had written a short description or copied the page title and made that the link. sometimes links will generate a rich preview at the bottom of the post, but those have bad UX problems so i usually remove them. can't rely on rich previews to add context.\n2. if anyone ever tries to read this convo with a screen reader, they're going to have to listen to a lot of gobbledegook.\nin the future, _please_ don't paste \"naked\" urls. write some text that _somehow_ suggests what the link is, and then make that text the link. thanks.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1772210829.823339",
    "parent_user_id": "UJFN50C00",
    "blocks": [
